{
  "texts": [
    "Kelly, Papanikolaou, Seru and Taddy (2021) show that these document links are indeed highly predictive of citation linkages.",
    "They leverage this idea to identify 'novel' and 'impactful' patents from 1850 to the present.",
    "A methological innovation in their approach is the use of a backward-looking variant of the TF-IDF Bag-of-Word embeddings, where the TF-IDF weights are dynamically updated as new innovations emerge.",
    "This approach may be desirable to identify important terms when the documents span long periods of time: the word 'electricity' is probably more informative about a patent's novelty in 1890 than in 1990.",
    "Moving beyond using the pairwise similarity among patent documents, Bergeaud, Schmidt and Zago (2022b) use the distance between patents and technical standards to measure the distance to the technological frontier."
  ]
}